hpEsFwVer.name: hpEsFwVer
hpEsFwVer.description: The firmware version in the form major.minor.

hpEsHwVer.name: hpEsHwVer
hpEsHwVer.description: The hardware version in the form major.minor.

hpEsIpAddr.name: hpEsIpAddr
hpEsIpAddr.description: The administrative value of the IP address. The current operational IP address can be obtained by the ipAdEntAddr entry in the ipAddrTable. This parameter will take effect only after a reset (hpEsReset) is issued or a power cycle.

hpEsNetMask.name: hpEsNetMask
hpEsNetMask.description: The administrative value of the subnet mask. The current operational subnet mask can be obtained by the ipAdEntNetMask entry in the ipAddrTable. This parameter will take effect only after a reset (hpEsReset) is issued or a power cycle.

hpEsDefaultGateway.name: hpEsDefaultGateway
hpEsDefaultGateway.description: The administrative value of the default gateway (router) IP address. The current operational default gateway's IP address can be obtained from the ipRouteTable. This parameter will take effect only after a reset (hpEsReset) is issued or a power cycle.

hpEsTrapRcvrMaxEnt.name: hpEsTrapRcvrMaxEnt
hpEsTrapRcvrMaxEnt.description: The maximum number of rows in the trap receiver table.

hpEsTrapRcvrCurEnt.name: hpEsTrapRcvrCurEnt
hpEsTrapRcvrCurEnt.description: The current number of rows in the trap receiver table.

hpEsTrapRcvrNext.name: hpEsTrapRcvrNext
hpEsTrapRcvrNext.description: The index of the next available row to be created in the trap receiver table. A value of zero means that the table is full and no more rows can be added.

hpEsTrapRcvrTable.name: hpEsTrapRcvrTable
hpEsTrapRcvrTable.description: A table of managers to which to send traps. Entries in the table are saved across resets and power cycles.

hpEsTrapRcvrEntry.name: hpEsTrapRcvrEntry
hpEsTrapRcvrEntry.description: Definition of rows in the trap receiver table. The column hpEsTrapRcvrStatus is used to create and delete rows in the table. Creation requires a SET PDU with objects hpEsTrapRcvrStatus, hpEsTrapRcvrIpAddress, and hpEsTrapRcvrComm.

hpEsTrapRcvrIndex.name: hpEsTrapRcvrIndex
hpEsTrapRcvrIndex.description: The index of the row in the table.

hpEsTrapRcvrStatus.name: hpEsTrapRcvrStatus
hpEsTrapRcvrStatus.description: Setting this object to the value invalid(3) deletes the row from the table. The value invalid(3) should never be returned on a GET. The value of create(4) on a SET causes a new row to be created if the row does not already exist. If it does, then a 'badValue'error should be returned. The value returned on GETs should be valid(2) or other(1), which is used to indicate any other condition.

hpEsTrapRcvrIpAddress.name: hpEsTrapRcvrIpAddress
hpEsTrapRcvrIpAddress.description: IP address for an SNMP manager that is to receive the trap.

hpEsNumPorts.name: hpEsNumPorts
hpEsNumPorts.description: The maximum number of ports on the switch.

hpEsNumStations.name: hpEsNumStations
hpEsNumStations.description: Aggregate number of currently active stations (nodes) on all ports on the switch. This is the value from the system module.

hpEsMostStations.name: hpEsMostStations
hpEsMostStations.description: Highest aggregate number of stations ever active on all ports at one time, since the last reset or power cycle. This is the value as seen by the system module.

hpEsMaxStations.name: hpEsMaxStations
hpEsMaxStations.description: Highest aggregate number of stations which the switch can support simultaneously. (This is the maximum number that the system module can support.)

hpEsReset.name: hpEsReset
hpEsReset.description: This object is used to reset the switch. Writing softReset(3) causes the switch to reset the hardware, run quick diagnostics, clear all counters, start switching, issue a warmstart trap, and then be able to respond to SNMP requests. Writing hardReset(4) causes the switch to run power up diagnostics and then execute a soft reset. Note: all address tables are cleared in both cases. The administrative parameters from nonvolatile memory are used to initialize the operational parameters. The value returned on GETs should be running(2) or other(1), which is used to indicate any other condition.

hpEsNumResets.name: hpEsNumResets
hpEsNumResets.description: Number of soft resets the switch has executed since the last hard reset or power cycle. Soft resets are defined as writing softReset(3) to hpEsReset, pressing the front panel reset button, executing a soft reset from the console, or resets induced by the switch firmware.

hpEsAddrAgingTime.name: hpEsAddrAgingTime
hpEsAddrAgingTime.description: Number of minutes of inactivity before an address entity is aged out. A value of zero means no aging. Note: if an address shows up on another port, the original port to address assignment is automatically deleted. The value is saved across resets and power cycles.

hpEsSysStaTable.name: hpEsSysStaTable
hpEsSysStaTable.description: A table of station addresses from all ports known to the system module.

hpEsSysStaEntry.name: hpEsSysStaEntry
hpEsSysStaEntry.description: Definition of the rows in the system module station address table. Rows can not be created or deleted via SNMP requests.

hpEsSysStaPort.name: hpEsSysStaPort
hpEsSysStaPort.description: The source port for the Station.

hpEsSysStaTraffic.name: hpEsSysStaTraffic
hpEsSysStaTraffic.description: A bit string that identifies with value of one of the ports that this station has generated traffic to or from. The bits are numbered starting at zero, with bit zero being the high order bit in the first byte, bit seven being the low order bit in the first byte, bit eight being the high order bit in the second byte, etc. Ports correspond with bits (i.e., port 1 is bit 1, etc.). The size of this in octets is the number of ports (i.e., hpEsNumPorts), divided by 8, plus one.

hpEsPortTable.name: hpEsPortTable
hpEsPortTable.description: A table of information about each port. The number of rows is given by hpEsNumPorts.

hpEsPortEntry.name: hpEsPortEntry
hpEsPortEntry.description: Definition of rows in the port table. The number of rows is determined by the hardware and is specified by the value of hpEsNumPorts. Rows can not be created or deleted via SNMP requests.

hpEsPortIndex.name: hpEsPortIndex
hpEsPortIndex.description: A unique value for each port entry. The value corresponds the port number.

hpEsPortOprStatus.name: hpEsPortOprStatus
hpEsPortOprStatus.description: The operational status of the port. Setting to enabled(1) enables the port. Setting to disabled(2) disables the port. The value is saved across resets and power cycles.

hpEsPortExtConn.name: hpEsPortExtConn
hpEsPortExtConn.description: Which external connector has been configured via jumpers. For EPS1500, this object will always return AUI.

hpEsPortDuplex.name: hpEsPortDuplex
hpEsPortDuplex.description: Indicates whether the port is jumper configured for full or half duplex operation. Note: internal connected ports are always halfDuplex(2).

hpEsPortRcvLocalFrames.name: hpEsPortRcvLocalFrames
hpEsPortRcvLocalFrames.description: Number of frames received where the destination is on this port.

hpEsPortForwardedFrames.name: hpEsPortForwardedFrames
hpEsPortForwardedFrames.description: Number of frames received on this port and forwarded to another port.

hpEsPortMostStations.name: hpEsPortMostStations
hpEsPortMostStations.description: Highest number of stations ever active at any time since the last reset of the switch as seen by this port.

hpEsPortMaxStations.name: hpEsPortMaxStations
hpEsPortMaxStations.description: Maximum number of stations which the port can support simultaneously.

hpEsPortSWHandledFrames.name: hpEsPortSWHandledFrames
hpEsPortSWHandledFrames.description: Number of Frames received on this port and delivered to the system module for processing.

hpEsPortLocalStations.name: hpEsPortLocalStations
hpEsPortLocalStations.description: Number of stations on this port which belong to the local segment.

hpEsPortRemoteStations.name: hpEsPortRemoteStations
hpEsPortRemoteStations.description: Number of stations on this port which belong to another segment.

hpEsPortUnknownStaFrames.name: hpEsPortUnknownStaFrames
hpEsPortUnknownStaFrames.description: Number of unicast frames received on this port and forwarded to the system module for processing because the source or destination station address is not in the port's forwarding table.

hpEsPortResetStats.name: hpEsPortResetStats
hpEsPortResetStats.description: Setting this object to reset(3) causes all traffic counters for this port to be set to zero. Also the value of hpEsPortResetTimer is set to zero.

hpEsPortResetTimer.name: hpEsPortResetTimer
hpEsPortResetTimer.description: Time (in 100th second ticks) since the port counters were reset.

hpEsPortResetAddrs.name: hpEsPortResetAddrs
hpEsPortResetAddrs.description: Setting this object to reset(3) clears all address table entries for this port as well as setting all port traffic counters to zero and setting hpEsPortResetTimer to zero.

hpEsPortRcvBcasts.name: hpEsPortRcvBcasts
hpEsPortRcvBcasts.description: Number of Broadcast Frames received on this port without errors.

hpEsPortSwitchedFrames.name: hpEsPortSwitchedFrames
hpEsPortSwitchedFrames.description: Number of frames switched on this port
